.SH "NAME"
ibist \- set individual status bit (board)
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.ft B
.nf
#include <gpib/ib\&.h>
.fi
.ft
.HP \w'int\ ibist('u
.BI "int ibist(int\ " "ud" ", int\ " "ist" ");"
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
If
\fIist\fR
is nonzero, then the individual status bit of the board specified by the board descriptor
\fIud\fR
is set\&. If
\fIist\fR
is zero then the individual status bit is cleared\&. The individual status bit is sent by the board in response to parallel polls\&.
.PP
On success,
iberr
is set to the previous ist value\&.
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.PP
The value of
ibsta
is returned\&.
